    <stitle>SPLIT AIR BRAKE SYSTEM - SPLIT AIR SYSTEM VALVES - RELAY VALVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>RELAY VALVE</title>
        <para>The relay valve (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0400810">Figure 10</hotlnk>) in a split air brake system functions as a relay station to
            speed up the application and release of the brakes. The valve is normally mounted close to the chamber it
            serves. The valve operates as a remote controlled brake valve that delivers or releases air to the chamber
            in response to the control air delivered to it from the brake valve or other source.
        </para>
